<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />
	</head>
	<body style="font-family:Arial, sans serif; background: whitesmoke">
		<br>
		<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="10%"></td>
				<td width="80%"><img src="http://#{Rails.application.secrets.domain}/images/email_header.png" alt="OpenSit"></td>
				<td width="10%"></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="10%"></td>
				<td style="background: white; border: 1px solid #CCC; padding: 20px" align="left" width="80%">
					<p>Hey,</p>
					<p>Just a quick email to let you know that the OpenSit blog is live!</p>
					<p><a style="font-weight:bold;" href="http://blog.#{Rails.application.secrets.domain}/opensit-is-your-community">Read the first post: OpenSit is your community</a>.
					<p>We have loads more planned for the blog:</p>
					<ul style="color:#666">
						<li>Tips and advice on meditation.</li>
						<li>Ways to improve your journalling.</li>
						<li>News and updates on contemplative research.</li>
						<li>Interviews, videos, and lots more!</li>
					</ul>
					<p>The best way to keep up with the blog is to follow @<%= link_to Rails.application.secrets.twitter_id, "https://twitter.com/#{Rails.application.secrets.twitter_id}" %> or <a href="http://blog.#{Rails.application.secrets.domain}/rss/">subscribe by RSS</a>.</p>
					<p>Happy sitting!</p>
					<p><%= Rails.application.secrets.public_person %><br><%= link_to Rails.application.secrets.domain, "http://#{Rails.application.secrets.domain}" %></p>
					<p>P.S. Follow us on <a href="https://twitter.com/#{Rails.application.secrets.twitter_id}">Twitter</a>, <a href="https://www.facebook.com/#{Rails.application.secrets.facebook_id}">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://www.google.com/+#{Rails.application.secrets.google_plus_id}">Google+</a> and <a href="http://github.com/danbartlett/opensit">GitHub</a> (we're open source!)</p>
				</td>
				<td width="10%"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<br><br><br>
	</body>
</html>
